 PHOTO: GOOGLE.COM/SEARCH  “Away from inflation figures, the steep decline in oil prices could be a threat to Nigeria’s economic recovery. If oil prices remain depressed and government revenues end up taking a hit, the impacts are likely to be reflected on the currency and inflation,” he said.
